== About me

Tsz Fai (Vincent) Chow is a research assistant professor at the [https://www.polyu.edu.hk/lms Department of Logistics and Maritime Studies] of [/https://www.polyu.edu.hk/ PolyU], Hong Kong. He received his PhD and MPhil in Systems Engineering and Engineering Management and BSc in Statistics from the [https://www.cuhk.edu.hk Chinese University of Hong Kong (CUHK)] in 2021, 2018, and 2016, respectively. Prior to joining PolyU, he was a postdoctoral fellow at CUHK.

Broadly speaking, his research interest includes all operations management problems that can be modeled as linear or mixed-integer programs. Applications considered in his work include surgery blocks allocation in [https://link.springer.com/book/10.1007/978-3-030-60212-3 healthcare], manpower (re)allocation in [https://link.springer.com/book/10.1007/978-1-4899-7571-3 public transit], and [https://link.springer.com/book/10.1007/978-3-030-32177-2 facility location problems].

He is constantly looking for ways that operations management, deep learning, and statistics can go together. In particular, his current research involves [https://doi.org/10.1016/j.tre.2022.102712 the use of reinforcement learning in combinatorial problems] which are notoriously hard to optimize. 
  
  
